questiontext.text:
Instructions

Select the correct solution from the dropdown menu in the following exercise:

1 The movement {1:MULTICHOICE:didn’t begin~have begun~=began} on September 16th,
2 when Mahsa Amini, whom Iran’s morality police {1:MULTICHOICE:have been arresting~don’t arrest~has arrested~=had arrested} for wearing her headscarf “improperly”,
4 Beyond their remarkable bravery, little {1:MULTICHOICE:doesn’t know~=is known~knew} for certain about the protesters
5 who {1:MULTICHOICE:=have thronged~am thronging~doesn’t throng~throngs} Iranian streets in recent months.
6 The worst event {1:MULTICHOICE:=was~am~are been} a march on September 30th,
7 in which protesters {1:MULTICHOICE:have sought~=sought~has sought~seeks} justice for a girl allegedly raped by a police chief.
8 Police {1:MULTICHOICE:was opening~=opened~didn’t open} fire
9 and {1:MULTICHOICE:kills~didn’t kill~was killing~=killed} 97 “marchers and rioters”.
10 Since then, the share of protests recorded as deadly {1:MULTICHOICE:falls~have fallen~=has fallen~have been falling} from 22% to 5%.

generalfeedback.text:
1 The movement began on September 16th,
2 when Mahsa Amini, whom Iran’s morality police had arrested for wearing her headscarf “improperly”,
4 Beyond their remarkable bravery, little is known for certain about the protesters
5 who have thronged Iranian streets in recent months.
6 The worst event was a march on September 30th,
7 in which protesters sought justice for a girl allegedly raped by a police chief.
8 Police opened fire
9 and killed 97 “marchers and rioters”.
10 Since then, the share of protests recorded as deadly has fallen from 22% to 5%.
